2️⃣ Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
1. Functional Requirements (FR)

User Module

FR1: Users shall be able to sign up/login using mobile/email.

FR2: Users shall be able to search for nearby bikes using GPS.

FR3: Users shall receive fare estimation before booking.

FR4: Users shall be able to make payments via digital methods.

FR5: Users shall track ride in real time.

FR6: Users can cancel or rate rides.

Vendor Module

FR7: Vendors shall receive booking requests in real-time.

FR8: Vendors can accept/decline bookings.

FR9: Vendors can update ride status (arrived, started, completed).

FR10: Vendors can view daily earnings and ride summary.

Admin Module

FR11: Admin shall manage users, vendors & bikes.

FR12: Admin can view real-time booking dashboards.

FR13: Admin shall approve vendor onboarding.

FR14: Admin can generate reports for operations & revenue.

2. Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)

Category	        Requirement
Performance	      App should load within 3 seconds.
Availability	    System uptime should be 99.5%.
Security	        All transactions must be encrypted (HTTPS/TLS).
Scalability	      System should handle 10,000+ concurrent users.
Usability	        Interface must follow standard UX guidelines.
Reliability	      Ride tracking must update every 5 seconds.

3. System Constraints

Mobile app must support Android 9+ and iOS 13+.

Integrates third-party payment gateway.

GPS accuracy dependent on device sensors.

Vendor must maintain valid documents for onboarding.
